_refine.details                                  
;1. HYDROGENS HAVE BEEN ADDED IN THE RIDING POSITIONS.
 2. A MET-INHIBITION PROTOCOL WAS USED FOR SELENOMETHIONINE
 INCORPORATION DURING PROTEIN EXPRESSION. THE OCCUPANCY
 OF THE SE ATOMS IN THE MSE RESIDUES WAS REDUCED TO 0.80
 TO ACCOUNT FOR THE REDUCED SCATTERING POWER DUE TO PARTIAL
 S-MET INCORPORATION.
 3. NI IONS ARE MODELED IN A PUTATIVE ACTIVE SITE BASED ON AN
 X-RAY FLUORESCENCE SCAN FOR METAL, ANOMALOUS DIFFERENCE
 FOURIERS, AND COORDINATION GEOMETRY.
 4. CA IONS FROM THE CRYSTALLIZATION CONDITIONS AND MRD
 MOLECULES FROM CRYO CONDITION ARE MODELED IN THE STRUCTURE.
;
